{"LanguageCode":"en","Chapter":80,"Index":"080","Name":"Abasa","TranslatedName":"He Frowned","ArabicName":"سُوْرَةُ عَبَسَ","Revelation":"Mecca","RevelationOrder":24,"VerseCount":42,"SajdaCount":0,"JuzStart":30,"JuzEnd":30,"VerseStart":5759,"VerseEnd":5800,"ManzilStart":7,"ManzilEnd":7,"RukuStart":522,"RukuEnd":522,"MaqraStart":234,"MaqraEnd":234,"PageStart":585,"PageEnd":585,"Summaries":["<p>42 verses in 1 section. The Surah begins with the incident of a blind man (Abdullah ibn Umm Maktum) who came to the Prophet to seek knowledge, while the chiefs of Makkah were denying the message. It talks about the greatness of Allah's message. Those who will accept this message they will benefit from it. But those who deny this message they are bringing harm to their own selves.</p>"],"Verses":[{"Verse":1,"Text":"عَبَسَ وَتَوَلَّىٰٓ","End":"١"},{"Verse":2,"Text":"أَن جَآءَهُ ٱلۡأَعۡمَىٰ","End":"٢"},{"Verse":3,"Text":"وَمَا يُدۡرِيكَ لَعَلَّهُۥ يَزَّكَّىٰٓ","End":"٣"},{"Verse":4,"Text":"أَوۡ يَذَّكَّرُ فَتَنفَعَهُ ٱلذِّكۡرَىٰٓ","End":"٤"},{"Verse":5,"Text":"أَمَّا مَنِ ٱسۡتَغۡنَىٰ","End":"٥"},{"Verse":6,"Text":"فَأَنتَ لَهُۥ تَصَدَّىٰ","End":"٦"},{"Verse":7,"Text":"وَمَا عَلَيۡكَ أَلَّا يَزَّكَّىٰ","End":"٧"},{"Verse":8,"Text":"وَأَمَّا مَن جَآءَكَ يَسۡعَىٰ","End":"٨"},{"Verse":9,"Text":"وَهُوَ يَخۡشَىٰ","End":"٩"},{"Verse":10,"Text":"فَأَنتَ عَنۡهُ تَلَهَّىٰ","End":"١٠"},{"Verse":11,"Text":"كَلَّآ إِنَّهَا تَذۡكِرَةٞ","End":"١١"},{"Verse":12,"Text":"فَمَن شَآءَ ذَكَرَهُۥ","End":"١٢"},{"Verse":13,"Text":"فِي صُحُفٖ مُّكَرَّمَةٖ","End":"١٣"},{"Verse":14,"Text":"مَّرۡفُوعَةٖ مُّطَهَّرَةِۭ","End":"١٤"},{"Verse":15,"Text":"بِأَيۡدِي سَفَرَةٖ","End":"١٥"},{"Verse":16,"Text":"كِرَامِۭ بَرَرَةٖ","End":"١٦"},{"Verse":17,"Text":"قُتِلَ ٱلۡإِنسَٰنُ مَآ أَكۡفَرَهُۥ","End":"١٧"},{"Verse":18,"Text":"مِنۡ أَيِّ شَيۡءٍ خَلَقَهُۥ","End":"١٨"},{"Verse":19,"Text":"مِن نُّطۡفَةٍ خَلَقَهُۥ فَقَدَّرَهُۥ","End":"١٩"},{"Verse":20,"Text":"ثُمَّ ٱلسَّبِيلَ يَسَّرَهُۥ","End":"٢٠"},{"Verse":21,"Text